19 January - 25 January
I joined the brainstorming process and discussed possible ideas for our application.

26 January - 1 February
We decided that our project would be a university-based marketplace application for Bilkent students and discussed its main features.

2 February - 8 February
We completed the Group Selection Stage Report.

9 February - 15 February
We completed the Requirements Stage Report.

16 February - 22 February
We discussed the database structure and decided to use MongoDB for our application.

23 February - 1 March
We worked on the user interface design and planned the layout of the main pages.

2 March - 8 March
We decided which libraries and technologies we would use in the project, such as JavaFX, FXML, MongoDB Java Driver, Jakarta Mail, and Maven.

9 March - 15 March
We completed the Detailed Design Report.

16 March - 22 March
Holiday week.

23 March - 29 March
I started implementing the JavaFX and FXML parts of the project. I focused on the UI structure and page organization.

30 March - 5 April
I implemented and improved several UI pages such as login, sign up, sell request, profile, product detail, leaderboard, and admin panel. I also worked on integrating UI components with the backend structure.

6 April - 12 April
I worked on the interactive features of the application, including e-mail verification, forgot password flow, profile editing, password changing, filtering, product detail actions, and seller-related operations. We also prepared the application for the demo.

